Microsoft plans big British plant - paper . Microsoft Corp chairman Bill Gates plans to set up a multi - million dollar electronics research campus in Cambridge , eastern England , the Daily Telegraph newspaper said on Saturday . It said the announcement of the company ' s first research base outside the United States is expected within weeks , and would turn the British university town into a technological powerhouse to rival Silicon Valley . The paper said Gates would separately make a major donation to Cambridge University to fund a new science block . The Telegraph quoted British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook as expressing his delight at the move . " This vote of confidence from the most successful exponent of computer software in the world proves that Britain is a global leader in this field and will act as a magnet for further inward investment , " he said . 
